# Ensemble Optimization

To combine the strengths of both models, a weighted ensemble strategy was employed.

The ensemble probability was calculated as:

Final Probability =
(Weight × LightGBM Probability)
+
((1 − Weight) × CatBoost Probability)

Multiple weights were evaluated and the optimal weight was determined automatically.

### Optimal Ensemble Weight

LightGBM Weight = 0.95

CatBoost Weight = 0.05

This indicates that LightGBM contributed most of the predictive power while CatBoost provided complementary improvements.

